Architecture plan for the static calculator

Product/name source
- The issues do not define a distinct product brand/name. Use generic calculator wording in project copy until an issue explicitly provides a name.

Project shape
- No-build static site served directly from repository files.
- Core files expected by the issue set:
  - index.html: semantic page shell, display region, button grid markup, script/style references.
  - styles.css: design tokens, page layout, display styling, button grid, interaction states, responsive polish.
  - calculator.js: calculator state, input transitions, arithmetic, display rendering, click and keyboard handlers.
  - README.md: static serving notes, manual verification checklist, deployment notes.

HTML/module structure
- Use a single calculator wrapper with semantic regions:
  - main app container.
  - output/display element with an accessible live label.
  - button grid with buttons annotated by data attributes such as data-action, data-value, and data-operator.
- Keep markup static and dependency-free so it works by opening or serving index.html.

CSS organization
- Define design tokens at :root:
  - muted/monochrome surface, text, border, and control colors.
  - one accent color reserved for operator and equals buttons.
  - sans-serif font stack, compact type scale, spacing scale, radius, and transition values.
- Organize styles in this order:
  - reset/base box sizing.
  - page shell.
  - calculator layout.
  - display.
  - button grid and button variants.
  - interaction states.
  - responsive adjustments.
- Maintain flat/minimal styling: no decorative gradients, heavy shadows, or unrelated visual assets.

JavaScript organization
- Keep calculator.js dependency-free and split behavior into small functions:
  - createInitialState/resetState.
  - inputDigit.
  - inputDecimal.
  - chooseOperator.
  - calculate/applyPendingOperation.
  - pressEquals.
  - clear.
  - formatDisplayValue.
  - render.
  - handleButtonAction.
  - handleKeyboardInput.
- Shared state shape:
  - currentEntry: string displayed/input value.
  - accumulatedValue: number or null.
  - pendingOperator: "+", "-", "*", "/" or null.
  - shouldStartNewEntry: boolean.
  - error: string or null for divide-by-zero/invalid states.
- Keep all input paths routed through the same transition functions so click and keyboard behavior stay identical.

Issue dependencies and sequencing
- Issue #1 establishes the static files and README.
- Issues #2-#5 build the UI foundation:
  - #2 page shell and tokens.
  - #3 display region.
  - #4 grid markup.
  - #5 button visual states.
- Issues #6-#10 build behavior:
  - #6 state model and display rendering for digits/decimal.
  - #7 button handlers.
  - #8 arithmetic and chained operations.
  - #9 edge guards.
  - #10 keyboard input on top of shared handlers.
- Issues #11-#13 finish quality and release:
  - #11 verification checklist in README.
  - #12 responsive visual polish.
  - #13 static deployment documentation.

Key design decisions
- Use strings for currentEntry to preserve user intent while typing decimals and leading zero transitions.
- Convert to numbers only at operation boundaries.
- Treat divide-by-zero as an explicit error state and render a clear indicator instead of Infinity or NaN.
- Make clear/reset globally valid, including from error state.
- Format results conservatively to avoid layout breakage while preserving readable precision.
- Prefer event delegation on the button grid over per-button listeners.
- Keyboard support should prevent default only for handled calculator keys.
- Verification can be lightweight manual/browser checks because the project has no build or test framework requirement.
